1.  Definitions

"Additional Use Grant" means the additional rights (if any) granted in the
Parameters section above. If the Additional Use Grant reads "None," no
additional rights are granted beyond those in Section 2.

"Change Date" means the date specified in the Parameters section above for
the applicable version of the Licensed Work.

"Change License" means the license identified in the Parameters section
above.

"Derivative Work" means any work that is based on, incorporates, or is a
modification of the Licensed Work.

"Non-Production Use" means use that is not directed toward a Production
Deployment. Non-Production Use includes, without limitation, personal study,
internal research and development, educational use, testing, prototyping, and
use in development or staging environments that are not accessible to end
users.

"Production Deployment" means any of the following: (a) deploying, verifying,
or causing to be deployed any smart contract or other executable code that
includes, is compiled from, or is a Derivative Work of, the Licensed Work on
any blockchain, distributed-ledger, or comparable network accessible by third
parties; (b) operating or making available to third parties any software
service, product, or system that incorporates the Licensed Work or a
Derivative Work; or (c) any other use of the Licensed Work or a Derivative
Work to process transactions, relay value, or provide services to third
parties.

"Separate Deployment Agreement" means a written agreement between you and the
Licensor (or its authorized representative) that expressly grants you the
right to make a Production Deployment of the Licensed Work or a Derivative
Work, subject to the terms and conditions set forth therein.

